<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="397" pageId="3" pageNumber="396" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1162,1979]" pageId="3" pageNumber="396">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1162,1187]" pageId="3" pageNumber="396">Description.</emphasis>
Body (
<figureCitation box="[428,493,1162,1187]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 5" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1979,2002]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,450,1953]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,448,1955]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 5. Squamiger elegans gen. et sp. nov. Hlaváč &amp; Baňař, male paratype: 1, dorsal habitus; 2, head, dorsal view; 3, pronotum, dorsal view; 4, detail of scale-like setae on pronotum; 5, elytra, dorsal view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258500/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="396">
Fig. 
<number box="[481,493,1163,1187]" pageId="3" pageNumber="396" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
) reddish-brown, antennae and legs slightly lighter. Setae on lateral and dorsal parts of body except abdomen broad and squamose. Head elongate, more than twice as long as wide, widest across eyes (
<figureCitation box="[159,230,1234,1259]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 5" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1979,2002]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,450,1953]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,448,1955]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 5. Squamiger elegans gen. et sp. nov. Hlaváč &amp; Baňař, male paratype: 1, dorsal habitus; 2, head, dorsal view; 3, pronotum, dorsal view; 4, detail of scale-like setae on pronotum; 5, elytra, dorsal view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258500/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="396">
Fig. 
<number box="[214,230,1235,1259]" pageId="3" pageNumber="396" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
), eyes large, about as long as temples, rostrum strongly projecting. Head capsule clearly demarcated by conspicuous occipital contriction from neck region (
<figureCitation box="[744,832,1270,1295]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 12" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1039,1062]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1018]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1018]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 12. Squamiger elegans gen. et sp. nov. Hlaváč &amp; Baňař, male paratype: 10, abdomen and apex of elytra, lateral view; 11, sternite IV, fovea and wrinkled area; 12, head, lateral view. (III—third antennomere; IV—fourth antennomere; Vfifth antennomere; bc — buccal cavity; gp — gular plate; occ — occipital constriction; pd — pedicel; sc — scape). Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258502/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="396">Figs 12</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[845,875,1271,1295]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 16" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1548,1571]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1526]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1527]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 16. Squamiger elegans gen. et sp. nov. Hlaváč &amp; Baňař, male paratype, ventral view: 13, habitus; 14, head; 15, prothorax, ventral view; 16, fused meso- and metaventrite. (bst — basistipes; cd — cardo; cl — clypeus; gp — gular plate; lb — labrum; md — mandible; mn — mentum; occ — occipital constriction; plp — palpomere; tp — tentorial pits). Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258503/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="396">14</figureCitation>
), antennal cavity broad and deep. Antennae (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 12" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1039,1062]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1018]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1018]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 12. Squamiger elegans gen. et sp. nov. Hlaváč &amp; Baňař, male paratype: 10, abdomen and apex of elytra, lateral view; 11, sternite IV, fovea and wrinkled area; 12, head, lateral view. (III—third antennomere; IV—fourth antennomere; Vfifth antennomere; bc — buccal cavity; gp — gular plate; occ — occipital constriction; pd — pedicel; sc — scape). Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258502/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="396">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,180,1307,1331]" pageId="3" pageNumber="396" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
) with five antennomeres, slightly longer than head in males, shorter than head in females. Terminal antennomere (V) inserted into IV, both subequal in length, antennomeres I–IV with the same cuticular surface as on rest of the head, with somewhat broadened setae, terminal antennomere roughly wrinkled, with normal, long, slender setae (
<figureCitation box="[159,233,1414,1439]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 9" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1736,1759]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1714]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,193,1716]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 9. Squamiger elegans gen. et sp. nov. Hlaváč &amp; Baňař, male paratype: 6, detail of antennomere V, anterior view; 7, elytral and abdominal trichomes; 8, laterodorsal habitus; 9, lateroventral habitus. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258501/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="396">Figs 6</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[246,277,1415,1439]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 12" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1039,1062]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1018]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1018]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 12. Squamiger elegans gen. et sp. nov. Hlaváč &amp; Baňař, male paratype: 10, abdomen and apex of elytra, lateral view; 11, sternite IV, fovea and wrinkled area; 12, head, lateral view. (III—third antennomere; IV—fourth antennomere; Vfifth antennomere; bc — buccal cavity; gp — gular plate; occ — occipital constriction; pd — pedicel; sc — scape). Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258502/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="396">12</figureCitation>
). Ventral part of head with tentorial pits distinctly separated. Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[1100,1168,1414,1439]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 5" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1979,2002]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,450,1953]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,448,1955]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 5. Squamiger elegans gen. et sp. nov. Hlaváč &amp; Baňař, male paratype: 1, dorsal habitus; 2, head, dorsal view; 3, pronotum, dorsal view; 4, detail of scale-like setae on pronotum; 5, elytra, dorsal view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258500/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="396">
Fig. 
<number box="[1154,1168,1415,1439]" pageId="3" pageNumber="396" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
) pentagonal, wider and shorter than head. Scutellum not visible. Elytra large, at suture slightly shorter than abdomen and about twice as long as pronotum, smooth, humeri inconspicuous, lacking foveae, each elytron with seven dorsal rows of setae. Posterior elytral margins with robust trichomes. Dorsum of abdomen shiny, composite tergite (IV–VI) shorter than elytra, with deep and large basal impression and two lateral trichomes located opposite tergal trichomes. Tergites VII and VIII very short, barely visible in dorsal view. First visible paratergites with long trichomes. Prosternum (
<figureCitation box="[159,245,1630,1655]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 16" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1548,1571]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1526]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1527]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 16. Squamiger elegans gen. et sp. nov. Hlaváč &amp; Baňař, male paratype, ventral view: 13, habitus; 14, head; 15, prothorax, ventral view; 16, fused meso- and metaventrite. (bst — basistipes; cd — cardo; cl — clypeus; gp — gular plate; lb — labrum; md — mandible; mn — mentum; occ — occipital constriction; plp — palpomere; tp — tentorial pits). Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258503/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="396">
Fig. 
<number box="[216,245,1630,1655]" pageId="3" pageNumber="396" value="15.0">15</number>
</figureCitation>
) with long prosternal process narrowly separating procoxae, mesoventrite and metaventrite confluent, shiny, both with fine longitudinal wrinkles on their lateral parts. Mesoventrite in middle with prominent keel (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 9" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1736,1759]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1714]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,193,1716]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 9. Squamiger elegans gen. et sp. nov. Hlaváč &amp; Baňař, male paratype: 6, detail of antennomere V, anterior view; 7, elytral and abdominal trichomes; 8, laterodorsal habitus; 9, lateroventral habitus. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258501/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="396">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,166,1703,1727]" pageId="3" pageNumber="396" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
) separating, together with metaventral anterior process, mesocoxae. Metaventrite with sharp median projection pointing posteroventrally (
<figureCitation box="[458,531,1738,1763]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 9" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1736,1759]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1714]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,193,1716]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 9. Squamiger elegans gen. et sp. nov. Hlaváč &amp; Baňař, male paratype: 6, detail of antennomere V, anterior view; 7, elytral and abdominal trichomes; 8, laterodorsal habitus; 9, lateroventral habitus. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258501/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="396">
Fig. 
<number box="[515,531,1739,1763]" pageId="3" pageNumber="396" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
). Metacoxae broadly separated by very wide and short posterior metaventral process (
<figureCitation box="[255,342,1774,1799]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 16" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1548,1571]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1526]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1527]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 16. Squamiger elegans gen. et sp. nov. Hlaváč &amp; Baňař, male paratype, ventral view: 13, habitus; 14, head; 15, prothorax, ventral view; 16, fused meso- and metaventrite. (bst — basistipes; cd — cardo; cl — clypeus; gp — gular plate; lb — labrum; md — mandible; mn — mentum; occ — occipital constriction; plp — palpomere; tp — tentorial pits). Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258503/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="396">
Fig. 
<number box="[311,342,1774,1799]" pageId="3" pageNumber="396" value="16.0">16</number>
</figureCitation>
). First visible sternite (III) about half as long as second sternite, second visible sternite (IV) longest, about as long as sternites V–VIII combined, with two well-defined lateral foveae, its lateral fourths between foveae and lateral margins conspicuously wrinkled (
<figureCitation box="[850,936,1846,1871]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 20" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1183,1206]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,195,1160]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,195,1162]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 20. Squamiger elegans gen. et sp. nov. Hlaváč &amp; Baňař, male paratype: 17, head, anterior view; 18, head, anteroventral view; 19, left middle tibia, inner view; 20, abdomen, ventral view. (bc — buccal cavity; cd — cardo; cl — clypeus; fr — frons; lb — labrum; md — mandible; mn — mentum; pd — pedicel; plp — palpomere; sc — scape). Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258504/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="396">
Fig. 
<number box="[904,936,1847,1871]" pageId="3" pageNumber="396" value="20.0">20</number>
</figureCitation>
). Legs short, tibiae pedunculate, mesotibiae with minute thorn in males (
<figureCitation box="[468,550,1882,1907]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 20" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1183,1206]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,195,1160]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,195,1162]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 20. Squamiger elegans gen. et sp. nov. Hlaváč &amp; Baňař, male paratype: 17, head, anterior view; 18, head, anteroventral view; 19, left middle tibia, inner view; 20, abdomen, ventral view. (bc — buccal cavity; cd — cardo; cl — clypeus; fr — frons; lb — labrum; md — mandible; mn — mentum; pd — pedicel; plp — palpomere; sc — scape). Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258504/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="396">
Fig. 
<number box="[520,550,1883,1907]" pageId="3" pageNumber="396" value="19.0">19</number>
</figureCitation>
), femora clavate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1162,1979]" pageId="3" pageNumber="396">
Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[328,462,1918,1943]" captionStart="FIGURES 21 – 22" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1977,2000]" captionTargetBox="[415,1171,975,1955]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[415,1171,975,1955]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 21 – 22. Squamiger elegans gen. et sp. nov. Hlaváč &amp; Baňař, male paratype, aedeagus: 21, dorsal view; 22, lateral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258505/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="396">
Figs 
<number box="[389,462,1919,1943]" pageId="3" pageNumber="396" value="21.5" valueMax="22.0" valueMin="21.0">21−22</number>
</figureCitation>
) symmetrical, parameres fused to median lobe, basal bulb semispherical, distinctly shorter and well-delimited from slender, long and at apex narrow apical lobe, dorsal diaphragm large, oval.
</paragraph>
